.TH "igb_write_8bit_ctrl_reg" 9 "igb_write_8bit_ctrl_reg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
igb_write_8bit_ctrl_reg \- Write a 8bit CTRL register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "s32" igb_write_8bit_ctrl_reg
.BI "(struct e1000_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u32 reg "  ","
.BI "u32 offset "  ","
.BI "u8 data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the HW structure
.IP "reg" 12
32bit register offset such as E1000_SCTL
.IP "offset" 12
register offset to write to
.IP "data" 12
data to write at register offset

Writes an address/data control type register.  There are several of these
and they all have the format address << 8 | data and bit 31 is polled for
completion.
